semantic_equivalence_artifact.original_latex_theorem:
\label{thm:rate}
	The method has a linear rate of convergence. For any $\btheta_{t} \neq 0$:
	\begin{align*}
	\frac{\caL(\btheta_{t + 1})}{\caL(\btheta_{t})} \leq \max_s\left(\frac{(A_s - a_s)^2}{(A_s + a_s)^2} \right) ,
	\end{align*}
	where $a_s = \min \mathrm{Sp}(\bH_s)$ and $A_s = \max \mathrm{Sp}(\bH_s)$. 
	Moreover, this rate is optimal, since it is possible to build $\btheta_t$
	such that:
	\begin{align*}
	\frac{\caL(\btheta_{t + 1})}{\caL(\btheta_{t})} = \max_s\left(\frac{(A_s - a_s)^2}{(A_s + a_s)^2} \right) .
	\end{align*}

